content.description: Start in cave underneath Leg Rash. There are some great jugs underneath. There will be a swing. Your feet will likely be in the water. The crux is either shared with Leg Rash or it is the exhaustive groping done when searching for the jug outside the cave (long arms help). High quality and rough sandstone. Shoes help a lot if you are soft and your feet can't handle the friction required.
content.location: About half way around Presque Isle point trail heading south from the Stockton Island Visitor Center.

content.description: Start in water. Reach for obvious jug. Crux is the first move which is a hard cross out right with your left hand. Get high feet. Move the right hand over and pull hard. Easiest with dry rubber (unlikely). Real hard when barefoot.
content.protection: Water. Not to be done during stormy weather or high waves.
content.location: Head South on trail from Stockton Island Visitor Center. About half way around the Presque Isle Point you at the first great walk out you will see a large rock broken off from the island. This is the area of the Boulder and the location of the easy access in and out of Lake Superior.
